definitions.definition: A surname transferred from the given name , a variant of Elliott .
A male given name from Hebrew , a variant of Elliott .
A coastal hamlet near Arbroath , Angus council area, Scotland ( OS grid ref NO6139 ) .
A town in the Eastern Cape province, South Africa , named after Henry George Elliot .
